{
  "narration": "You and your companions settle into a familiar corner of the Black Lantern Hearth, the warmth from the crackling peat fire a welcome relief after the night air. The tavern is quieter at this hour, with only a few villagers murmuring over mugs of ale near the hearth. \n\nGrimjaw, the gold-toothed proprietor, eyes the party with his usual calculating look but, recognizing you as the heroes of Marrow's Rest, he gestures brusquely to the bar. \"Well, don't just stand about -- bowls of stew, as promised for those who keep my roof standing!\" he calls, his voice gruff but not unfriendly. An unnamed serving girl quickly brings over steaming bowls brimming with hearty root vegetables, salted fish, and thick slices of black bread. \n\nScout Kira grins as she takes her bowl, nudging Eirik with her elbow. \"See? All it takes is a little saving the village and suddenly we're treated like proper guests.\"\n\nElen sniffs the stew with approval and raises her spoon in a silent toast. Thane, ever reserved, simply digs in, but even his stern features soften in the glow of the hearth. \n\nThe scent of herbs and slow-cooked broth fills your senses. For a fleeting moment, the troubles outside seem distant, replaced by warmth, camaraderie, and the simple satisfaction of a hot meal among friends. As you eat, you sense hopeful glances from the other villagers; your presence is a balm in these uneasy times.\n\nWhen you're ready, you may discuss strategy, question Grimjaw or Elder Dorun, or simply enjoy the respite before your next move into the unknown.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 15
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "With bellies full of stew and the warmth of the Black Lantern Hearth still clinging to your cloaks, you rise from your table, gathering your trusted companions for the journey ahead. Kira flashes a confident grin, tightening the straps on her quiver, while Elen checks her bow and Thane nods his readiness, his eyes reflecting the flicker of the hearth one last time.\n\nGrimjaw, ever the watchful proprietor, raises his mug in a rare gesture of respect. \"Best keep your wits about you, heroes,\" he mutters. \"Doom's not just in a name out there.\"\n\nElder Dorun, sitting quietly by the fire, offers a final word of encouragement. \"Bring back hope, Eirik. Marrow's Rest will look to your light.\"\n\nAs you step into the night, the air is brisk and thick with the promise of rain. The village fades behind you as you make your way to the edge of the mist, the road twisting toward a fate both uncertain and formidable. Hours pass in contemplative silence and subtle preparation as the landscape shifts--from the salt-worn paths of Kharos to the tangled forests and looming silhouette of the Keep of Doom.\n\nCresting a wooded hill, you see the worn rooftops of Harrow's Hollow clustered in the keep's shadow, the stones of the fortress standing stark against the star-strewn sky. The next chapter of your adventure begins here, with new allies and threats awaiting in the haunted halls and winding streets below.\n\nWhat is your first move in Harrow's Hollow? Will you seek out the general store, scout the keep's perimeter, or gather rumors among the wary locals?",
