{
  "narration": "As the deep night settles over Marrow's Rest, you and your companions gather near the crackling hearth of the Black Lantern Hearth. The tavern is unusually quiet at this hour, its shadows long and the air thick with the scent of peat smoke. Grimjaw, gold teeth gleaming in the dim glow, wipes a mug with his battered rag and eyes your party with wary respect. At your request, he produces a fresh round of ale, sliding sturdy mugs across the worn bar. \"A nightcap for brave souls, eh? Just don't let the mists steal you away,\" he mutters, offering a crooked grin.\n\nKira accepts her ale with a flourish, tapping her mug against yours. \"To surviving another night in the Hollow,\" she toasts, her eyes bright with mischief. Elen and Thane raise their drinks as well, sharing silent camaraderie. The warmth of the fire and the taste of the ale settle your nerves, giving you and your friends a brief, much-needed respite from the darkness pressing in outside.\n\nFor a few moments, the world beyond the tavern's sturdy walls feels distant, and you have space to enjoy the company of your allies and the comfort of simple pleasures. When you are ready, you can discuss your next steps or seek out a conversation with Elder Dorun, Captain Merek, or even Grimjaw himself.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 10
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "With the hour deep into the night, you and your companions make your decision. Kira wipes the foam from her ale and flashes you a bright, determined grin. \"Well, if we're bound for doom, at least our bellies are full,\" she jokes, slinging her pack over her shoulder. Thane finishes his drink and stands, his gaze steady and resolute, while Elen double-checks her bow and gear, a cautious optimism flickering in her eyes. Grimjaw gives a parting nod from behind the bar, his gruff voice low. \"Watch your backs out there. And don't bring any curses back to my hearth.\"\n\nThe tavern's warmth gives way to the chill of the misty streets as you step outside. The lantern-lit lanes of Marrow's Rest quickly fade behind, replaced by the winding road through shadowed woods and ancient stones. Hours pass in anticipation as the landscape transforms around you--distant howls, the rustle of unseen creatures, and the looming silhouette of Harrow's Hollow beneath the shadow of the Keep of Doom.\n\nAt last, the fortress rises before you, its black stones stark against the star-sworn sky and the silent village clustered below. The air is heavy with secrets and the promise of new trials. Your party stands at the threshold of a new adventure, braced for whatever darkness might linger within those walls.\n\nWhat would you like to do first in Harrow's Hollow? Seek out the general store, scout the keep's perimeter, or listen for rumors among the wary locals?",
