{
  "narration": "You finish the last of your ale, the taste lingering as you gather your companions for the journey ahead. Kira slings her quiver and flashes a lopsided grin, Elen checks the straps on her pack, and Thane gives a curt nod, his silhouette outlined in the first glow of dawn. The Black Lantern Hearth is already stirring behind you, Elder Dorun watching quietly from his corner as you step out into the briny morning air.\n\nThe lanes of Marrow's Rest give way to the tangled forest road, mist curling through the gnarled trunks as you press eastward. Hours pass in thoughtful silence--the only sounds are the crunch of boots on gravel and the distant rush of surf. The sky brightens to a pale spring blue, then dims again under the looming shadow of a new horizon.\n\nBy mid-morning, the rooftops and battered palisade of Harrow's Hollow rise before you, huddled beneath the ancient, brooding walls of the Keep of Doom. The air is thick with tension and the promise of secrets to come. As you cross into the village, wary faces peer from shuttered windows, and the ruined keep stands sentinel above all.\n\nYou and your companions have arrived at the threshold of your next great adventure. Will you seek out supplies at the general store, investigate the villagers' troubles, or approach the keep itself to begin your exploration?",
