{
  "narration": "With your gear checked and your companions ready, you rise from your place near the hearth. Kira gives you a lopsided grin, slinging her quiver over her shoulder. \"Another trip through the mists, Trouble Magnet?\" she teases, her tone light but her eyes steeled by resolve. Elen and Thane fall in beside you, their movements efficient and practiced. \n\nElder Dorun, catching your eye from his quiet corner, offers a solemn nod. \"May the light guide your steps, and may hope find you in darker halls,\" he says softly.\n\nThe familiar scents and comforts of the Black Lantern Hearth fade quickly as you step into the pale spring sunlight. The streets of Marrow's Rest are still, and a salty breeze rides over the rooftops. Your footsteps soon carry you down the winding path away from the village, past old standing stones and through thickets of tangled woods. The world grows quieter and more foreboding as the hours pass, until at last, the silhouette of Harrow's Hollow and the towering, shadow-cast walls of the Keep of Doom rise ahead.\n\nThe village is subdued beneath the keep's gaze, the streets unusually empty this late in the morning. Your party stands at the threshold of a new chapter--the keep's secrets and dangers waiting just beyond. Do you wish to seek out supplies first, gather rumors among the locals, or approach the keep directly?",
